Attacks in the Netherlands cannot be ruled out. Attacks could be indiscriminate, including in places frequented by expatriates and foreign travellers. You should be vigilant and follow the advice of local authorities. On 28 August 2018, two foreign tourists were seriously injured in a knife attack at Amsterdam Central Station.
